  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The spelling tool we're using for the Python and documentation is pretty limited, and it doesn't actually enforce a single consistent spelling (it allows `initialise` and `initialize`, for example.) I would like to see us improve the tool, and specifically add a feature for choosing a specific English spelling flavour.\r\n\r\nI propose we use Canadian English spelling, since I'm Canadian, and would enjoy aggravating both our European and American contributors.",
